id: jf-n0m4
title: Prevent shell injection through manual release workflow inputs
description: "Manual release workflows interpolate workflow_dispatch inputs directly into run-script source. A ref, tag, or confirmation value containing quotes or shell metacharacters can change the generated shell program. Pass all GitHub expression values through step-level environment variables, quote shell expansions, and add workflow lint/static validation."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 0
tags[4]: github-actions,release,security,workflow-injection
created_at: "2026-07-16T16:51:57.099Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-16T17:00:22.677Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-16T17:00:22.676Z"
author: codex
acceptance_criteria: "No workflow_dispatch input is interpolated directly inside a run script.; Release confirmation, tag, ref, and metadata behavior remains unchanged for valid inputs."
goal: jf-mqpo
parent: jf-kpor
severity: high
environment: "GitHub Actions workflow_dispatch in release-github.yml, release-publish.yml, and release-prepare.yml"
repro_steps: Inspect run blocks containing direct workflow input expression interpolation; supply a value containing a single quote and shell operator.
resolution: "Moved confirmation, tag, and ref values into step environment variables and quoted all shell reads."
expected_result: Dispatch inputs are data rather than generated shell source.
actual_result: No workflow run block directly interpolates workflow_dispatch input expressions.
customer_impact: An authorized workflow dispatcher can unintentionally or maliciously execute altered commands with release workflow permissions.
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-16T17:00:05.312Z",codex,All workflow_dispatch values used by shell scripts now enter through step env variables; no direct input expressions remain inside run-script source.
files[3]{path,scope,note}:
  .github/workflows/release-github.yml,project,tag and confirmation input boundary
  .github/workflows/release-publish.yml,project,publish confirmation boundary
  .github/workflows/release-prepare.yml,project,release metadata ref boundary
close_reason: Manual release input shell boundaries are hardened.
body: ""
